09/06/83   apply, ap

Syntax:  apply {-control_args} command_line


Function:  Places the current query into a temporary file, adds the
pathname of this file to the end of the supplied command line, and
executes the resulting Multics command line.  If there is no current
query or the control argument -new is used, the created file is
initially empty.


Control Arguments:

-new
   specifies that an empty file should initially be created.

-old
   specifies that the existing query should be made available
   (DEFAULT).


Examples:

apply -new ted -pn
apply emacs
